As the world's top arms exporter, the U.S. and its military-industrial complex are profiteering from the Russia-Ukraine conflict. Many countries call for a peaceful resolution through dialogue, but some fuel the fire for profit. The military-industrial complex in the United States is skilled at lobbying the government to get more defense contracts by inciting tensions. They never care about the tears of refugees trapped by war but only money filling their pockets. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Cao Yi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)